  "market_context": "New York session open (9:30 ET) on Friday, Aug 11, 2023. Price had swept a prior high, fallen back into range, and the analyst monitored the ES/NQ ratio chart for early reversal signals before confirming on individual index charts.",
  "key_observation": "At 9:30 and 9:35, the ES/NQ ratio formed reversal patterns (high followed by drop) *before* ES and NQ individually formed their reversals, with NQ showing relative strength (closing above prior high) while ES struggled to break its prior hour candle high.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst observed the ES/NQ ratio chart forming a reversal at 9:30 — price swept a high then fell back inside the range, signaling potential reversal.",
    "Step 2: Analyst checked ES and NQ 5-minute charts and confirmed a reversal candle formed on both at the 9:30 open, validating the ratio signal.",
    "Step 3: Analyst noted relative strength: NQ closed above its prior high while ES failed to break above its prior hour candle high, confirming NQ stronger/ES weaker.",
    "Step 4: At 9:35, analyst identified another ES/NQ ratio low (reversal setup), which preceded the actual ES/NQ high at 10:00 and subsequent drop — NQ led the reversal signal again before ES confirmed at 10:05."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "The ES/NQ ratio acts as a leading intermarket indicator: reversals in the ratio often precede and confirm reversals on individual index charts, especially when paired with relative strength analysis (NQ vs ES).",
